---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const standards = {
  backend: [
    "architecture",
    "api",
    "database",
    "error-handling",
    "observability",
    "python",
    "security",
    "testing",
  ],
  frontend: [
    "react",
    "typescript",
    "accessibility",
    "performance",
    "testing",
    "data-management",
    "logging",
  ],
  infrastructure: ["ci-cd", "docker"],
  operations: ["runbooks", "feature-flags"],
  crossCutting: ["RULES.yaml", "markdown-format-specification"],
};
---

<Base title="Standards" description="The 21 standards docs cadence scaffolds.">
  <h1>Standards catalog</h1>
  <p>
    Cadence ships 21 standards docs across five scopes. Each scaffolds into
    <code>auto/standards/&lt;scope&gt;/&lt;name&gt;.md</code> as an opinionated
    ~300-line markdown body cross-referenced to rule IDs in
    <code>RULES.yaml</code>.
  </p>

  <p>
    Scaffold one with <code>cadence add standard &lt;scope&gt;/&lt;name&gt;</code>,
    e.g. <code>cadence add standard backend/architecture</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Backend ({standards.backend.length})</h2>
  <ul>{standards.backend.map((s) => <li><code>backend/{s}</code></li>)}</ul>

  <h2>Frontend ({standards.frontend.length})</h2>
  <ul>{standards.frontend.map((s) => <li><code>frontend/{s}</code></li>)}</ul>

  <h2>Infrastructure ({standards.infrastructure.length})</h2>
  <ul>{standards.infrastructure.map((s) => <li><code>infrastructure/{s}</code></li>)}</ul>

  <h2>Operations ({standards.operations.length})</h2>
  <ul>{standards.operations.map((s) => <li><code>operations/{s}</code></li>)}</ul>

  <h2>Cross-cutting ({standards.crossCutting.length})</h2>
  <ul>{standards.crossCutting.map((s) => <li><code>cross-cutting/{s}</code></li>)}</ul>

  <h2>Why scaffold vs depend</h2>
  <p>
    Standards docs encode opinions: "always async endpoints," "tenant_id in
    every query." Those opinions belong in your repo because they evolve
    per team. Cadence gives you a starting point and the runtime to execute
    against it — same model that made shadcn click.
  </p>
</Base>
